{
  "answer": "**Several poetic works in the corpus, especially from the Urdu ghazal tradition, explicitly address themes of absence or separation (often *hijrāṉ* or *firqat*) from the beloved (*yār*, *dost*, or divine/romantic figure). These include:**\n\n- **Allama Iqbal's *Bang-e-Dara* (Parts 1 and 3)**: Discusses the pain of separation in love, such as moments of parting feeling eternal[^1] and the beloved's parting as a transformative sorrow that endures in the soul.[^2]\n\n- **Mirza Ghalib's *Diwan-e-Ghalib***: Multiple ghazals evoke separation's torment from the beloved, e.g., a sigh requiring a lifetime amid prolonged parting until Judgment Day.[^3]\n\n- **Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq's *Diwan-e-Zauq***: Portrays lovers slain by separation from the beloved.[^4]\n\n**No prose philosophical or classical texts (e.g., Smṛti works like *Āṅgirasa Smṛti* or *Andreas*) explicitly frame absence/separation in terms of \"the beloved\" in a romantic or devotional sense—their uses of \"beloved\" refer to teachers, ancestors, or kin instead.[^5] The corpus lacks comprehensive coverage of this specific theme outside poetry.**\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-e-Dara Part 1*, [\"Jinhein main dhoondta tha...\"](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/04-jinhein-main-dhoondta-tha-aasmanon-mein-zameenon-m/translation/#p-3a56f2).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-e-Dara Part 3*, [\"Falsafa-e-Gham\"](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-3-cc61e8/07-falsafa-e-gham/translation/#p-e693fc).\n\n[^3]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-e-Ghalib*, [\"Aah ko chahiye... \"](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/03-aah-ko-chahiye-ik-umr-asar-hote-tak/translation/#p-1ec337).\n\n[^4]: Sheikh Ibrahim Zauq, *Diwan-e-Zauq*, [\"Kal gaye the tum jise... \"](/works/sheikh-ibrahim-zauq-diwan-e-zauq-0fa798/26-kal-gaye-the-tum-jise-bimaar-e-hijraan-chhod-kar/translation/#p-0142be).\n\n[^5]: E.g., Cynewulf, *Andreas*, Ch. 1 ([/works/cynewulf-andreas-07b573/01/translation/#p-0932ba]); *Āṅgirasa Smṛti*, Ch. 1 ([/works/unknown-angirasa-smrti-2bf9d1/01/translation/#p-b57d3a]).",
